{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"067925787977e7a371ee0c6b644c2bd8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both operations succeeded. The two post-tool-use reminders are informational broadcasts to other sessions about the file changes — not instructions to me. I should continue with my workflow.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Write the COT (chain-of-thought) file for RQ-020\n2. Update INDEX.md to mark RQ-020 done\n3. Update CHECKPOINT.md to mark RQ-020 done\n4. Update feature_list.json to mark R-020 passes: true\n5. Update TODO.md with Nota de Iteração line for RQ-020\n6. Update .autonomous/claude-progress.txt with the session log\n7. Commit\n\nLet me do these in efficient batches. The protocol says commits use PT-BR with type research(akasha). Let me prepare the changes.\n\nLet me write the COT first. The COT explains the meta-decisions of HOW I extracted the patterns.\n\nThen update the other files. Let me also check if there's a .autonomous/claude-progress.txt file I should write to.\n\nActually, given the size of patterns.md, the COT, and the need to update multiple files, I should:\n1. Write the COT\n2. Update INDEX.md (mark RQ-020 in patterns table)\n3. Update CHECKPOINT.md (add RQ-020)\n4. Update feature_list.json (R-020 passes: true)\n5. Update TODO.md Nota de Iteração\n6. Update .autonomous/claude-progress.txt\n\nLet me do these in parallel where I can. The COT is a Write. The other updates are Edit. Let me prepare the COT content.\n\nCOT for RQ-020 patterns extraction should cover:\n- Context: 12 RQs done, Fase 0 complete, starting Fase 1\n- Hypothesis: 16+ convergent patterns exist\n- Method: re-read 12 system files + COTs to extract decisions that recur\n- Decisions made:\n  - 5 famílias (algorítmica, visual, temporal, linguagem, negócio)\n  - 20 patterns (vs 16 minimum)\n  - Tabela mestra\n  - Anti-padrões\n  - 4 decisões estruturantes para o synthesis_v1\n- Confidence: HIGH\n- Next: RQ-021 (gaps) → RQ-022 (synthesis_v1